items.team_description: Afghanistan was granted test status in 2017, and currently hold the record for the highest T20I total, scoring 278-3 against Ireland in 2019. They have appeared in 2 one-day World Cups.
Cricket Australia are the joint oldest menâ€™s Test cricket history, playing in the first ever Test in 1877. They have held the number one ranking in all forms of international cricket.
The Tigers first played international cricket in 1979, gaining Test status in 2000. Achievements include reaching the 2015 World Cup quarter-final and semi-final of the 2017 ICC Champions Trophy.
England were involved in the first ever menâ€™s Test match, in 1877. They won the ICC World Cup in 2019, as well as the T20 World Cup in 2022, holding both titles simultaneously.
Team India have won 5 major ICC titles in limited-over cricket, and finished runner-up in the 2019-2021 World Test Championship. They have won the one-day World Cup twice, the latest in 2011.
Ireland acquired Test status in 2017 and have appeared in 3 World Cups and 7 T20 World Cups. In 2011 Ireland shocked the world by beating England in the World Cup.
The Black Caps played their first Test match in 1930 against England. They have never won the One-Day or T20 World Cups, but did win the 2019-2021 World Test Championship.
The Men in Green have achieved historical success in all forms of the game, winning each of the major ICC international tournaments. Most recently they won the T20 World Cup in 2009.
The Proteas are one of the major players on the international scene, having held the number one ranking in every form at times â€“ however â€“ they have never won a major ICC tournament.
The Lions first played international cricket in 1926-27. They shocked the world when they won the World Cup in 1996 and lifted the T20 title in 2014.
The Windies are a multi-national team, representing countries and territories of the Caribbean. They have lifted the T20 World Cup on two occasions, in 2012 and 2016.
The Zimbabwe cricket team gained Test status in 1992. They have appeared in 9 World Cups as well as 6 T20 World Cups, the first appearance coming in 2007.
